      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:2:55:3",
      "text": [
        " طَلَاقُ الْأَخْرَسِ أَنْ يَأْخُذَ مِقْنَعَتَهَا فَيَضَعَهَا عَلَى رَأْسِهَا وَ يَعْتَزِلَهَا ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Al Nowfaly, from Al Sakuny, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘A divorce of the mute is that he takes her veil, so he places it upon her head, and he takes it off’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "3. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from al-Nawfaliy from al-Sakuniy who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘Divorce by a speechless man can happen by his placing her headscarf on her head and then taking it away from her head.’” "
        ]
      }
    },
